Chapter 4 — SEO System & Content Strategy
4.1 Purpose

SEO exists to help people discover valuable educational content.

Search engine optimization should never reduce readability.

Every optimization must improve the user experience first and search engine visibility second.

The primary goal is to create tutorials that deserve to rank because they provide the best answer to the reader's question.

4.2 SEO Philosophy

Every article must satisfy three audiences:

Human readers
Search engines
AI assistants and answer engines

Human readers always have the highest priority.

4.3 Target Keyword

Every article must have one primary keyword.

Examples:

ESP32 OLED Tutorial
MPU6050 Arduino
DS3231 Arduino
I2C Scanner
HC-SR04 ESP32

Choose only one primary keyword.

Everything else becomes secondary keywords.

4.4 Keyword Placement

The primary keyword should naturally appear in:

Page title
URL
H1 heading
First paragraph
At least one H2
Meta description
One image alt text
Conclusion

Avoid forcing the keyword into every paragraph.

4.5 Secondary Keywords

Each article should target 5–15 related phrases.

Example for an OLED tutorial:

SSD1306
ESP32 OLED
Arduino OLED
I2C Display
OLED Display
SSD1306 Library
Wire Library
Display Text
ESP32 Screen

Use them naturally throughout the article.

4.6 Search Intent

Before writing, identify the user's intent.

Common intents:

Learn

"What is I²C?"

Build

"ESP32 OLED Tutorial"

Solve

"ESP32 OLED not working"

Compare

"ESP32 vs Arduino"

Every article should clearly satisfy one or more of these intents.

4.7 Title Rules

Titles should:

Clearly describe the content
Include the primary keyword
Be concise
Encourage clicks without exaggeration

Recommended length:

50–60 characters.

